n rules()\r\n    {\r\n        return [\r\n            [\r\n                ['a_id'],\r\n                'exist',\r\n                'targetClass' => A::class,\r\n                'targetAttribute' => ['a_id' => 'id', 'foo_id'],  // shortcut 'foo_id' as documented before\r\n            ],\r\n        ];\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo, `B::foo_id == A::foo_id` and `B::a_id == A::id`\r\n\r\nA:\r\n\r\nid | foo_id\r\n-- | --\r\n42 | 997\r\n\r\n```php\r\n$b = new B();\r\n$b->foo_id = 997;\r\n$b->a_id = 42;\r\n\r\nif (!$b->save()) {\r\n    \\Yii::error($b->errors);\r\n    throw ...;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is the expected result?\r\n\r\n```mysql\r\nSELECT EXISTS(SELECT * FROM `a` WHERE (`id`=42) AND (`foo_id`=997))\r\n```\r\n\r\nValidation passed.\r\n\r\n### What do you get instead?\r\n\r\n```mysql\r\nSELECT EXISTS(SELECT * FROM `a` WHERE (`id`=42) AND (`foo_id`=42))\r\n```\r\n\r\nValidation failed: `Attribute \"a_id\" is incorrect`.\r\n\r\n### Additional info\r\n\r\nFix code as such:\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n- [['a_id'], 'exist', 'targetClass' => A::class, 'targetAttribute' => ['a_id' => 'id', 'foo_id']]\r\n+ [['a_id'], 'exist', 'targetClass' => A::class, 'targetAttribute' => ['a_id' => 'id', 'foo_id' => 'foo_id']]\r\n```\r\n\r\n| Q                | A\r\n| ---------------- | ---\r\n| Yii version      | 2.0.11.1\r\n| PHP version      | 7.0.13\r\n| Operating system | Ubuntu 16.04\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"cebe","id":189796,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4OTc5Ng==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/189796?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/cebe","html_url":"https://github.com/cebe","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cebe/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cebe/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cebe/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cebe/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cebe/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https